I dont think it is the engine being tired (8K on its first rebuild); it may
very well be that the infamous 'sweet spot' is 55 MPH as it will drive all
day at that speed.

My concern (I may be spazzing again <g>) is my general inexperience with VW
engines.  Two years ago I had never driven a VW.  After I got the bus (part
of my need to get a life), I bought a couple of books and hooked up on the
internet.  Now I have am having the time of my life after an engine rebuild
and a growing list of things I had never done before.  Unlike most people
out there that have been driving busses for years, I (guess) my biggest
problem is having a reasonable point of reference.

In some unscientific experiments (my wife followed me down a stretch of road
a while back), it appears that the speedo is OK.  I have pretty complete
maintenance records (I have stuff from the original owner who had it for
over 30 years), and there are no indication of it having tranny work.

I am good with 55MPH

