my 61 15 window I usually drive it about 60, but I accidently took it up to
70 once -that was before I put the small tires on front, so it had 205 75
15s
all around - 1600sp, 4.37r/p, 1.26 rg.   had a 59 truck with little nut
tranny and 40hp motor, lots of zip, but I tried to keep it to 52mph, or it
would whine -  I could take it up to 60mph, but it really was very  unhappy
there.  Could pull hills fully loaded though.  There is a difference between
what the bus can be pushed to go, and where the sweet spot is.  I don't mind
being passed on the freeway, it's so stylee to drive an old bus.

Is your speedo accurate?  When you go max speed is it whining with excessive
rpms or just not enough oomph.   If the latter maybe your motor is getting
tired (compression check?)   But maybe not.  You say the bus is stock? How
do
you know what the gearing is, unless you have complete records since bus was
new?  The tranny that came to me in my 65 westy had a bug 4th gear in it-
that does drop top speed.

